EasyOverrider

Enum ParamUsage

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ParamUsage>
      • EasyOverrider.ParamUsage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ParamUsage>

    public enum ParamUsage
extends Enum<ParamUsage>
    Enum to make it easier to dictate which methods a parameter should be included in.
    • INCLUDED_IN_ALL
    • TOSTRING_ONLY
    • EQUALS_AND_HASHCODE_ONLY
    • IGNORED_FOR_ALL
    • EQUALS_ONLY__UNSAFE
    • HASHCODE_ONLY__UNSAFE
    • HASHCODE_AND_TOSTRING_ONLY__UNSAFE
    • EQUALS_AND_TOSTRING_ONLY__UNSAFE
    Entries that end in __UNSAFE should only be used in extreme circumstances.
    The rule is that if objA.equals(objB) then objA.hashCode() must equal objB.hashCode(). By including a parameter in equals but not hashCode, there's a very good chance of breaking that part of the contract. By including a parameter in hashCode but not equals, you run the risk of things not working right when they rely on the hashCode. For example, a hashSet might falsely identify two different entries as the same.
